52.1	Juggernaut	Juggernaut	A juggernaut ) in colloquial English usage is a literal or metaphorical force regarded as mercilessly destructive and unstoppable. Originating ca. 1850, the term is a metaphorical reference to the Hindu Ratha Yatra temple car, which apocryphally was reputed to crush devotees under its wheels.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Juggernaut_-_Project_Gutenberg_eBook_11921.jpg/220px-Juggernaut_-_Project_Gutenberg_eBook_11921.jpg
